Commentary Text: Mustafizur to Ashwin, byes, 2 runs, absolute comedy of errors! A scene straight out of the slapstick comedy of Indian cinema this. So it's an off-cutter from Mustafizur, Ashwin wants the reverse paddle but never connects. Then wants a bye but is never making it to the other end, or so it seems. Samson's throw to Mustafizur is good enough for the run out but the Fizz fails with the shy at the bowler's end, allowing an extra run. Gee, that's quite a lot of tragedy in the same delivery

Commentary Text: Rahul Tewatia to Shreyas Iyer, out Stumped!! This is a massive breakthrough! It was a bit of a punt to bowl Tewatia this over but also a clever move. Iyer was clearly going to target the part-timer and perishes in the process. Probably premeditated the charge a wee bit and it allowed Tewatia to float this much wider outside off. Iyer isn't quite able to reach it and Samson is quick to whip the bails off. The RR skipper was confident and replays show why. Iyer's back foot had already gone out of the crease and it was only whether his bat had gotten back in before the bails were dislodged. It hadn't. RR bossing this innings at the moment. Shreyas Iyer st Samson b Rahul Tewatia 43(32) [4s-1 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Mustafizur to Pant, out Bowled!! The Fizz has struck! He was brought on to break this partnership and with both batters starting to hit out, you'd think it was the right move to bring Mustafizur back. He's not the easiest to hit away, especially on these slow decks. This is another of his cutters, on a hard length and Pant makes the mistake of trying to pull with too much force. Only manages an under-edge onto the sticks. Just when he was starting to open up, the DC skipper has to go. Pant b Mustafizur 24(24) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: Kartik Tyagi to Dhawan, out Bowled!! Played on! That's unlucky for Dhawan, but Tyagi continues to impress - short of a good length and around the off-stump line, Dhawan was looking to defend with soft hands, he does so and the ball unfortunately rolls back and hits the base of leg-stump. A slow-motion dismissal for the prolific left-hander, but the Royals have struck early. On replays, the ball did clip the back of the pad on its way to the stumps. Dhawan b Kartik Tyagi 8(8) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Ashwin to Miller, out Stumped!! Delhi Capitals on top as Ashwin strikes in his first over, just like Nortje and Avesh Khan did. Miller shimmies down the wicket against Ashwin and has a wild swing. The ball doesn't turn at all, keeps straight, beats the batsman all ends up and Pant is waiting behind to complete the formalities. No chance of getting back as the Royals are three down. Two of their most dangerous hitters are back to the hut within the powerplay. Miller st Pant b Ashwin 7(10)

Commentary Text: Nortje to Samson, no run, Sanju Samson has been adjudged caught behind. But he has decided to challenge the call. He reckons it came off the shoulder. And I think the decision has to be overturned. Nothing on UltraEdge, and the decision has been reversed. Was a sharp bouncer by Nortje and Samson got beaten on his hook. Misses the top-edge, smacks his shoulder/ helmet and lobs towards Pant who dives in front of him to grab it. Would have been a fantastic take had there been bat or glove involved. This is some serious fast bowling by Nortje

Commentary Text: Nortje to Jaiswal, out Caught by Pant!! Just the kind of start Delhi Capitals would have wanted. Both the openers are back to the pavilion as Avesh and Nortje have struck on successive deliveries. Too hot to handle for the inxperience of Jaiswal - Nortje's pace. Pitched up outside off and the ball shapes away ever so slightly. Jaiswal has a poke and gets a feather. It was a loud noise and Pant was sure that Jaiswal was gone. Jaiswal c Pant b Nortje 5(4)

Commentary Text: Avesh Khan to Livingstone, out Caught by Pant!! Avesh Khan strikes in his first over! Livingstone was down the track early, and Avesh Khan is smart enough to bang it in. A short and slow ball, and the batsman gets a bottom edge as he is way too early in his pull. Pant dives in front of him and takes the catch inches above the ground. Livingstone won't get many chances to bat up the order, so he should have taken his time, rather than throwing it away so early. Livingstone c Pant b Avesh Khan 1(3)
